        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "\nI have found that ActionStack does not act as expected (well, at least as I expected it to act) when forwarding.\nUsing a Controller's _forward will disable ViewRenderer auto rendering, while using ActionStack to forward will not.\n\nFrom the manual: \n\"If you perform a _forward(), redirect, or render manually, autorendering will not occur, as by performing any of these actions you are telling the ViewRenderer that you are determining your own output.\" (http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.controller.actionhelpers.html)\n\nI suggest to have the option (which in my opinion should true by default, since an ActionStack is a forwarding stack), to disable ViewRenderer auto render in ActionStack."
        },
