        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18844",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This would only make sense *if* you use the action helper to add to the stack *from* a controller; in any other situation, the application will have no context. Here's why.\n\nActionStack is two separate components, a helper and a plugin. The helper simply provides an easy way to add items to the stack maintained in the plugin, while the plugin does the actual work. The plugin operates during the postDispatch() that occurs during the front controller dispatch loop.\n\nThe ViewRenderer renders during the postDispatch of the *action controller*. It has no awareness of the ActionStack at all.\n\nFurthermore, the primary use case of the ActionStack is for building widget-ized or composite layouts. When using ActionStack, you should in most cases render to a separate response segment so that you can later pull out the individual pieces of content to build the final output.\n\nWith that in mind, if you are using the ActionStack and *don't* want such behaviour, you can easily turn off auto-rendering at either the controller level or in your own plugins and action helpers (or subclass the ActionStack to add this behaviour).\n\nI'm not making a decision at this point as to whether or not to honor your request as I want to see if there is additional feedback from other users.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-05T09:08:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-05T09:08:59.000+0000"
                },
